  doctrineandcovenants,31,7,"Yea, I will open the hearts of the people, and they will receive you. And I will establish a church by your hand;","12:16:TG Conversion."
  doctrineandcovenants,31,8,And you shall strengthen them and prepare them against the time when they shall be gathered.,"14:24:Zech. 10:12; D&C 81:5; 108:7."
  doctrineandcovenants,31,9,"Be patient in afflictions, revile not against those that revile. Govern your house in meekness, and be steadfast.","3:10:Rom. 12:12. TG Patience.|14:25:TG Affliction.|27:33:TG Forbear; Malice; Retribution; Reviling.|77:82:TG Family, Love within.|103:112:TG Steadfastness."
  doctrineandcovenants,31,10,"Behold, I say unto you that you shall be a physician unto the church, but not unto the world, for they will not receive you.",""
  doctrineandcovenants,31,11,"Go your way whithersoever I will, and it shall be given you by the Comforter what you shall do and whither you shall go.","67:76:TG Holy Ghost, Comforter."
  doctrineandcovenants,31,12,"Pray always, lest you enter into temptation and lose your reward.","0:4:TG Prayer.|33:43:Mark 14:38. TG Temptation.|58:64:TG Reward."
  doctrineandcovenants,31,13,"Be faithful unto the end, and lo, I am with you. These words are not of man nor of men, but of me, even Jesus Christ, your Redeemer, by the will of the Father. Amen.","3:11:TG Steadfastness.|21:24:Rev. 2:10.|39:43:Matt. 28:20.|140:144:TG Jesus Christ, Authority of."
  doctrineandcovenants,32,1,"And now concerning my servant Parley P. Pratt, behold, I say unto him that as I live I will that he shall declare my gospel and learn of me, and be meek and lowly of heart.",""
  doctrineandcovenants,32,2,"And that which I have appointed unto him is that he shall go with my servants, Oliver Cowdery and Peter Whitmer, Jun., into the wilderness among the Lamanites.",""
  doctrineandcovenants,32,3,"And Ziba Peterson also shall go with them; and I myself will go with them and be in their midst; and I am their advocate with the Father, and nothing shall prevail against them.",""
  doctrineandcovenants,32,4,"And they shall give heed to that which is written, and pretend to no other revelation; and they shall pray always that I may unfold the same to their understanding.",""
  doctrineandcovenants,32,5,"And they shall give heed unto these words and trifle not, and I will bless them. Amen.",""
  doctrineandcovenants,33,1,"Behold, I say unto you, my servants Ezra and Northrop, open ye your ears and hearken to the voice of the Lord your God, whose word is quick and powerful, sharper than a two-edged sword, to the dividing asunder of the joints and marrow, soul and spirit; and is a discerner of the thoughts and intents of the heart.","36:40:D&C 52:22; 56:5 (5–8).|126:130:Heb. 4:12; Hel. 3:29 (29–30).|292:299:Amos 4:13."
