  doctrineandcovenants,38,25,"And again I say unto you, let every man esteem his brother as himself.","51:58:Acts 17:26 (26–34)."
  doctrineandcovenants,38,26,"For what man among you having twelve sons, and is no respecter of them, and they serve him obediently, and he saith unto the one: Be thou clothed in robes and sit thou here; and to the other: Be thou clothed in rags and sit thou there—and looketh upon his sons and saith I am just?","276:280:TG God, Justice of."
  doctrineandcovenants,38,27,"Behold, this I have given unto you as a parable, and it is even as I am. I say unto you, be one; and if ye are not one ye are not mine.","92:95:John 17:21 (21–23); 1 Cor. 1:10; Eph. 4:13 (11–14); 3 Ne. 11:28 (28–30); Moses 7:18. TG Unity."
  doctrineandcovenants,38,28,"And again, I say unto you that the enemy in the secret chambers seeketh your lives.","77:82:D&C 5:33 (32–33); 10:6 (6, 25); 38:13; 42:64."
  doctrineandcovenants,38,29,"Ye hear of wars in far countries, and you say that there will soon be great wars in far countries, but ye know not the hearts of men in your own land.","11:15:D&C 42:64; 45:63 (26, 63); 87:2 (1–5); 130:12."
  doctrineandcovenants,38,30,"I tell you these things because of your prayers; wherefore, treasure up wisdom in your bosoms, lest the wickedness of men reveal these things unto you by their wickedness, in a manner which shall speak in your ears with a voice louder than that which shall shake the earth; but if ye are prepared ye shall not fear.","60:68:JS—M 1:37.|72:78:TG Study; Wisdom."
  doctrineandcovenants,38,31,"And that ye might escape the power of the enemy, and be gathered unto me a righteous people, without spot and blameless—","42:47:TG Enemies.|101:105:2 Pet. 3:14."
  doctrineandcovenants,38,32,"Wherefore, for this cause I gave unto you the commandment that ye should go to the Ohio; and there I will give unto you my law; and there you shall be endowed with power from on high;","46:57:D&C 42:3.|83:87:D&C 37:3.|123:126:D&C 42:2 (1–93).|151:158:Luke 24:49; D&C 39:15; 43:16; 95:8 (8–9); 110:9 (9–10)."
  doctrineandcovenants,38,33,"And from thence, whosoever I will shall go forth among all nations, and it shall be told them what they shall do; for I have a great work laid up in store, for Israel shall be saved, and I will lead them whithersoever I will, and no power shall stay my hand.","40:48:TG Missionary Work.|176:181:Isa. 45:17; Jer. 30:10; 31:7 (6–7); Hosea 13:9; D&C 136:22.|194:198:TG Guidance, Divine.|245:249:Dan. 4:35."
  doctrineandcovenants,38,34,"And now, I give unto the church in these parts a commandment, that certain men among them shall be appointed, and they shall be appointed by the voice of the church;","128:137:TG Delegation of Responsibility.|145:150:TG Sustaining Church Leaders."
  doctrineandcovenants,38,35,"And they shall look to the poor and the needy, and administer to their relief that they shall not suffer; and send them forth to the place which I have commanded them;","71:77:TG Welfare."
  doctrineandcovenants,38,36,"And this shall be their work, to govern the affairs of the property of this church.","76:82:TG Church Organization."
  doctrineandcovenants,38,37,"And they that have farms that cannot be sold, let them be left or rented as seemeth them good.",""
  doctrineandcovenants,38,38,"See that all things are preserved; and when men are endowed with power from on high and sent forth, all these things shall be gathered unto the bosom of the church.","52:59:TG Endowment; Genealogy and Temple Work."
  doctrineandcovenants,38,39,"And if ye seek the riches which it is the will of the Father to give unto you, ye shall be the richest of all people, for ye shall have the riches of eternity; and it must needs be that the riches of the earth are mine to give; but beware of pride, lest ye become as the Nephites of old.","19:25:2 Ne. 26:31; Jacob 2:18 (17–19); D&C 11:7. TG Objectives.|190:196:Hag. 2:8.|242:247:Prov. 11:2; 2 Ne. 26:20 (20–22). TG Pride.|271:279:Moro. 8:27."
  doctrineandcovenants,38,40,"And again, I say unto you, I give unto you a commandment, that every man, both elder, priest, teacher, and also member, go to with his might, with the labor of his hands, to prepare and accomplish the things which I have commanded.","151:156:TG Industry.|164:169:1 Cor. 4:12."
  doctrineandcovenants,38,41,"And let your preaching be the warning voice, every man to his neighbor, in mildness and in meekness.","13:22:TG Preaching.|30:37:TG Warn.|91:99:Titus 3:2."
  doctrineandcovenants,38,42,And go ye out from among the wicked. Save yourselves. Be ye clean that bear the vessels of the Lord. Even so. Amen.,"10:13:Isa. 52:11.|29:35:Ps. 26:4; Rom. 12:9.|60:65:Lev. 21:6; Ether 12:37."
  doctrineandcovenants,39,1,"Hearken and listen to the voice of him who is from all eternity to all eternity, the Great I Am, even Jesus Christ—","55:63:Heb. 13:8; D&C 20:12; 35:1; 38:1 (1–4); 76:4. TG Eternity."
  doctrineandcovenants,39,2,The light and the life of the world; a light which shineth in darkness and the darkness comprehendeth it not;,"4:9:TG Jesus Christ, Light of the World."
  doctrineandcovenants,39,3,"The same which came in the meridian of time unto mine own, and mine own received me not;","27:43:D&C 20:26; Moses 5:57; 6:57 (57, 62); 7:46.|72:87:TG Prophets, Rejection of."
  doctrineandcovenants,39,4,"But to as many as received me, gave I power to become my sons; and even so will I give unto as many as will receive me, power to become my sons.","57:61:John 1:12. TG Sons and Daughters of God."
  doctrineandcovenants,39,5,"And verily, verily, I say unto you, he that receiveth my gospel receiveth me; and he that receiveth not my gospel receiveth not me.","64:73:John 13:20.|90:99:TG Teachable."
  doctrineandcovenants,39,6,"And this is my gospel—repentance and baptism by water, and then cometh the baptism of fire and the Holy Ghost, even the Comforter, which showeth all things, and teacheth the peaceable things of the kingdom.","15:21:TG Baptism; Gospel; Repent.|75:90:TG Holy Ghost, Baptism of; Holy Ghost, Comforter; Holy Ghost, Mission of.|161:169:D&C 36:2; 42:61."
  doctrineandcovenants,39,7,"And now, behold, I say unto you, my servant James, I have looked upon thy works and I know thee.","44:49:D&C 40:1.|86:90:Gen. 18:19."
  doctrineandcovenants,39,8,"And verily I say unto thee, thine heart is now right before me at this time; and, behold, I have bestowed great blessings upon thy head;","112:121:Prov. 10:6."
  doctrineandcovenants,39,9,"Nevertheless, thou hast seen great sorrow, for thou hast rejected me many times because of pride and the cares of the world.","35:41:Mosiah 7:29.|57:65:John 12:48; Alma 10:6.|118:123:Matt. 13:22; Hel. 7:5."
  doctrineandcovenants,39,10,"But, behold, the days of thy deliverance are come, if thou wilt hearken to my voice, which saith unto thee: Arise and be baptized, and wash away your sins, calling on my name, and you shall receive my Spirit, and a blessing so great as you never have known.","29:40:TG Deliver.|64:71:D&C 40:3 (1–3).|135:139:TG Baptism, Essential; Purity; Repent."
  doctrineandcovenants,39,11,"And if thou do this, I have prepared thee for a greater work. Thou shalt preach the fulness of my gospel, which I have sent forth in these last days, the covenant which I have sent forth to recover my people, which are of the house of Israel.","84:91:Rom. 15:29; D&C 18:4.|154:162:D&C 1:22.|190:197:TG Israel, Restoration of."
  doctrineandcovenants,39,12,"And it shall come to pass that power shall rest upon thee; thou shalt have great faith, and I will be with thee and go before thy face.","43:47:2 Cor. 12:9. TG Deliver; Guidance, Divine."
  doctrineandcovenants,39,13,"Thou art called to labor in my vineyard, and to build up my church, and to bring forth Zion, that it may rejoice upon the hills and flourish.","19:24:Matt. 20:8 (1–16).|48:53:D&C 30:6; 42:8.|60:66:TG Jesus Christ, Head of the Church.|87:91:Isa. 52:8.|132:140:D&C 35:24; 49:25; 117:7 (7–8)."
  doctrineandcovenants,39,14,"Behold, verily, verily, I say unto thee, thou art not called to go into the eastern countries, but thou art called to go to the Ohio.",""
  doctrineandcovenants,39,15,"And inasmuch as my people shall assemble themselves at the Ohio, I have kept in store a blessing such as is not known among the children of men, and it shall be poured forth upon their heads. And from thence men shall go forth into all nations.","88:96:D&C 38:32; 43:16; 95:8 (8–9); 110:9 (8–10).|232:235:D&C 1:2, 34 (34–35); 18:28 (26–28); 42:58.|236:243:TG Missionary Work."
  doctrineandcovenants,39,16,"Behold, verily, verily, I say unto you, that the people in Ohio call upon me in much faith, thinking I will stay my hand in judgment upon the nations, but I cannot deny my word.","108:112:2 Sam. 24:16; Moses 7:51.|164:168:2 Tim. 2:13."
  doctrineandcovenants,39,17,"Wherefore lay to with your might and call faithful laborers into my vineyard, that it may be pruned for the last time.","93:99:Jacob 5:61 (61–75); D&C 24:19; 95:4."
  doctrineandcovenants,39,18,"And inasmuch as they do repent and receive the fulness of my gospel, and become sanctified, I will stay mine hand in judgment.","117:125:TG Jesus Christ, Judge."
  doctrineandcovenants,39,19,"Wherefore, go forth, crying with a loud voice, saying: The kingdom of heaven is at hand; crying: Hosanna! blessed be the name of the Most High God.","83:87:Matt. 3:2."
  doctrineandcovenants,39,20,"Go forth baptizing with water, preparing the way before my face for the time of my coming;","9:18:TG Baptism, Essential.|83:89:TG Jesus Christ, Prophecies about; Jesus Christ, Second Coming."
  doctrineandcovenants,39,21,For the time is at hand; the day or the hour no man knoweth; but it surely shall come.,"29:32:Matt. 24:36; 1 Cor. 5:5.|52:59:JS—M 1:40.|81:85:Hab. 2:3."
  doctrineandcovenants,39,22,And he that receiveth these things receiveth me; and they shall be gathered unto me in time and in eternity.,"67:75:D&C 10:65."
  doctrineandcovenants,39,23,"And again, it shall come to pass that on as many as ye shall baptize with water, ye shall lay your hands, and they shall receive the gift of the Holy Ghost, and shall be looking forth for the signs of my coming, and shall know me.","99:104:TG Hands, Laying on of.|133:137:TG Holy Ghost, Gift of.|170:177:Rev. 3:3; D&C 35:15; 45:39.|204:210:2 Pet. 3:12."
  doctrineandcovenants,39,24,"Behold, I come quickly. Even so. Amen.",""
  doctrineandcovenants,40,1,"Behold, verily I say unto you, that the heart of my servant James Covel was right before me, for he covenanted with me that he would obey my word.","60:71:D&C 39:7."
  doctrineandcovenants,40,2,"And he received the word with gladness, but straightway Satan tempted him; and the fear of persecution and the cares of the world caused him to reject the word.","7:15:Mark 4:16.|62:69:TG Test.|91:102:Matt. 13:21 (20–22). TG Persecution.|144:150:TG Apostasy of Individuals."
  doctrineandcovenants,40,3,"Wherefore he broke my covenant, and it remaineth with me to do with him as seemeth me good. Amen.","13:18:D&C 39:10 (7–24)."
  doctrineandcovenants,41,1,"Hearken and hear, O ye my people, saith the Lord and your God, ye whom I delight to bless with the greatest of all blessings, ye that hear me; and ye that hear me not will I curse, that have professed my name, with the heaviest of all cursings.","12:16:Deut. 32:1.|115:124:TG Blessing.|174:179:Deut. 11:28; 1 Ne. 2:23; D&C 50:8. TG Curse.|191:200:D&C 50:4; 56:1; 112:26.|204:208:TG Jesus Christ, Taking the Name of."
  doctrineandcovenants,41,2,"Hearken, O ye elders of my church whom I have called, behold I give unto you a commandment, that ye shall assemble yourselves together to agree upon my word;","138:143:TG Unity."
  doctrineandcovenants,41,3,"And by the prayer of your faith ye shall receive my law, that ye may know how to govern my church and have all things right before me.","52:55:D&C 42:2 (1–93). TG God, Law of.|91:97:TG Jesus Christ, Head of the Church."
  doctrineandcovenants,41,4,"And I will be your ruler when I come; and behold, I come quickly, and ye shall see that my law is kept.","19:24:Zech. 14:9; 1 Tim. 6:15 (14–15); D&C 45:59. TG Governments.|32:36:TG Jesus Christ, Second Coming."
  doctrineandcovenants,41,5,"He that receiveth my law and doeth it, the same is my disciple; and he that saith he receiveth it and doeth it not, the same is not my disciple, and shall be cast out from among you;","8:17:Matt. 7:24.|21:24:Josh. 1:8; Jer. 26:4; Mosiah 3:14 (14–15); 13:29 (29–32); Alma 25:15 (15–16).|29:34:Rom. 2:13; James 1:22 (22–25); D&C 42:60.|102:107:Matt. 21:30. TG Hypocrisy.|158:166:D&C 42:37; 50:8 (8–9); 64:35. TG Excommunication."
  doctrineandcovenants,41,6,"For it is not meet that the things which belong to the children of the kingdom should be given to them that are not worthy, or to dogs, or the pearls to be cast before swine.","130:134:Matt. 15:26; Mark 7:27 (25–30).|143:149:Matt. 7:6. TG Holiness."
  doctrineandcovenants,41,7,"And again, it is meet that my servant Joseph Smith, Jun., should have a house built, in which to live and translate.","72:77:D&C 42:71 (70–73).|106:115:IE translate the Bible. D&C 37:1; 45:60–62; 73:3; 76:15; 93:53."
  doctrineandcovenants,41,8,"And again, it is meet that my servant Sidney Rigdon should live as seemeth him good, inasmuch as he keepeth my commandments.",""
  doctrineandcovenants,41,9,"And again, I have called my servant Edward Partridge; and I give a commandment, that he should be appointed by the voice of the church, and ordained a bishop unto the church, to leave his merchandise and to spend all his time in the labors of the church;","36:52:D&C 36:1; 42:10.|151:157:D&C 58:24 (14–24); 68:14; 72:6 (6, 9–12); 107:69 (69–75). TG Bishop.|207:212:D&C 51:1 (1–20); 57:7; 58:17 (14–18)."
  doctrineandcovenants,41,10,To see to all things as it shall be appointed unto him in my laws in the day that I shall give them.,""
  doctrineandcovenants,41,11,"And this because his heart is pure before me, for he is like unto Nathanael of old, in whom there is no guile.","66:75:John 1:47.|104:109:TG Guile."
  doctrineandcovenants,41,12,"These words are given unto you, and they are pure before me; wherefore, beware how you hold them, for they are to be answered upon your souls in the day of judgment. Even so. Amen.","136:141:TG Accountability; Responsibility."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,1,"Hearken, O ye elders of my church, who have assembled yourselves together in my name, even Jesus Christ the Son of the living God, the Savior of the world; inasmuch as ye believe on my name and keep my commandments.","27:33:TG Jesus Christ, Head of the Church."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,2,"Again I say unto you, hearken and hear and obey the law which I shall give unto you.","52:55:Jer. 26:4; D&C 41:3; 43:2; 58:23. TG God, Law of."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,3,"For verily I say, as ye have assembled yourselves together according to the commandment wherewith I commanded you, and are agreed as touching this one thing, and have asked the Father in my name, even so ye shall receive.","76:87:D&C 38:32.|133:141:Matt. 18:19."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,4,"Behold, verily I say unto you, I give unto you this first commandment, that ye shall go forth in my name, every one of you, excepting my servants Joseph Smith, Jun., and Sidney Rigdon.","85:93:TG Mission of Latter-day Saints."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,5,"And I give unto them a commandment that they shall go forth for a little season, and it shall be given by the power of the Spirit when they shall return.","97:102:TG Guidance, Divine; Holy Ghost, Mission of."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,6,"And ye shall go forth in the power of my Spirit, preaching my gospel, two by two, in my name, lifting up your voices as with the sound of a trump, declaring my word like unto angels of God.","70:80:Mark 6:7; Rom. 10:14. TG Gospel; Missionary Work.|140:145:Isa. 58:1."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,7,"And ye shall go forth baptizing with water, saying: Repent ye, repent ye, for the kingdom of heaven is at hand.",""
  doctrineandcovenants,42,8,And from this place ye shall go forth into the regions westward; and inasmuch as ye shall find them that will receive you ye shall build up my church in every region—,"131:136:D&C 30:6; 39:13."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,9,"Until the time shall come when it shall be revealed unto you from on high, when the city of the New Jerusalem shall be prepared, that ye may be gathered in one, that ye may be my people and I will be your God.","84:88:D&C 57:2.|96:109:Ether 13:6 (2–11); D&C 45:66 (66–71); 48:4; 64:30; 84:2, 4 (2–5); Moses 7:62; A of F 1:10. TG Jerusalem, New.|144:152:TG Israel, Gathering of.|179:185:Zech. 8:8."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,10,"And again, I say unto you, that my servant Edward Partridge shall stand in the office whereunto I have appointed him. And it shall come to pass, that if he transgress another shall be appointed in his stead. Even so. Amen.","43:59:D&C 41:9 (9–11); 50:39; 124:19.|103:112:TG Delegation of Responsibility.|167:174:D&C 35:18 (17–18); 64:40; 104:77; 107:99 (99–100)."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,11,"Again I say unto you, that it shall not be given to any one to go forth to preach my gospel, or to build up my church, except he be ordained by some one who has authority, and it is known to the church that he has authority and has been regularly ordained by the heads of the church.","75:81:TG Missionary Work; Preaching.|132:140:TG Called of God; Priesthood, Authority; Priesthood, Ordination; Priesthood, Qualifying for.|161:170:Acts 18:27. TG Authority; Leadership."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,12,"And again, the elders, priests and teachers of this church shall teach the principles of my gospel, which are in the Bible and the Book of Mormon, in the which is the fulness of the gospel.","15:21:TG Elder, Melchizedek Priesthood.|65:70:Mosiah 18:19 (19–20); D&C 5:10; 31:4; 52:9 (9, 36). TG Education; Mission of Latter-day Saints; Priesthood, Magnifying Callings within.|131:145:TG Book of Mormon.|167:174:Rom. 15:29; D&C 35:17; 135:3. TG Scriptures, Value of.|182:188:TG Gospel."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,13,"And they shall observe the covenants and church articles to do them, and these shall be their teachings, as they shall be directed by the Spirit.","15:22:TG Commitment.|27:56:IE D&C 20 (see the section 20 heading). D&C 1:6 (6, 37); 33:14; 51:4; 68:24.|60:62:D&C 84:57.|122:130:Gal. 5:18."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,14,And the Spirit shall be given unto you by the prayer of faith; and if ye receive not the Spirit ye shall not teach.,"39:41:D&C 63:64. TG Prayer.|89:95:Ex. 35:34; 1 Cor. 4:20. TG Holy Ghost, Mission of; Missionary Work; Teacher; Teaching; Teaching with the Spirit."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,15,"And all this ye shall observe to do as I have commanded concerning your teaching, until the fulness of my scriptures is given.","46:55:TG Commandments of God.|106:116:D&C 35:20; 42:56 (56–58)."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,16,"And as ye shall lift up your voices by the Comforter, ye shall speak and prophesy as seemeth me good;","43:52:2 Pet. 1:21; D&C 18:32; 34:10; 68:3."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,17,"For, behold, the Comforter knoweth all things, and beareth record of the Father and of the Son.","17:26:1 Cor. 2:10. TG Holy Ghost, Comforter.|51:58:D&C 1:39; 20:27. TG Holy Ghost, Source of Testimony."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,18,"And now, behold, I speak unto the church. Thou shalt not kill; and he that kills shall not have forgiveness in this world, nor in the world to come.","57:61:Ex. 20:13 (13–17); Deut. 5:17 (17–21); Matt. 5:21 (21–37); Mosiah 13:21 (21–24); 3 Ne. 12:21 (21–37).|75:80:TG Life, Sanctity of; Murder.|87:90:D&C 76:34; 84:41; 132:27."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,19,"And again, I say, thou shalt not kill; but he that killeth shall die.","51:58:TG Blood, Shedding of.|65:68:TG Capital Punishment."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,20,Thou shalt not steal; and he that stealeth and will not repent shall be cast out.,"34:42:TG Stealing.|72:80:Zech. 5:3."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,21,Thou shalt not lie; he that lieth and will not repent shall be cast out.,"15:18:Luke 18:20. TG Honesty; Lying."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,22,"Thou shalt love thy wife with all thy heart, and shalt cleave unto her and none else.","11:15:TG Family, Love within; Love; Marriage, Continuing Courtship in; Marriage, Husbands; Marriage, Wives.|55:61:Gen. 2:24 (23–24); D&C 49:15 (15–16); Moses 3:24 (23–24); Abr. 5:18 (17–18). TG Divorce."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,23,"And he that looketh upon a woman to lust after her shall deny the faith, and shall not have the Spirit; and if he repents not he shall be cast out.","12:19:2 Sam. 11:2. TG Carnal Mind; Lust.|96:102:D&C 63:16. TG Holy Ghost, Loss of."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,24,"Thou shalt not commit adultery; and he that committeth adultery, and repenteth not, shall be cast out.","22:30:Ezek. 18:6; Luke 18:20; D&C 63:14.|55:63:TG Adulterer; Sexual Immorality.|93:101:Prov. 6:33 (32–33)."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,25,"But he that has committed adultery and repents with all his heart, and forsaketh it, and doeth it no more, thou shalt forgive;","98:105:John 8:11. TG Forgive."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,26,"But if he doeth it again, he shall not be forgiven, but shall be cast out.","19:24:Ps. 85:8; 2 Pet. 2:20."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,27,"Thou shalt not speak evil of thy neighbor, nor do him any harm.","15:25:Prov. 3:29. TG Gossip; Slander."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,28,Thou knowest my laws concerning these things are given in my scriptures; he that sinneth and repenteth not shall be cast out.,"93:102:TG Repent.|116:124:TG Excommunication; Punish."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,29,If thou lovest me thou shalt serve me and keep all my commandments.,"8:14:John 14:15 (15, 21). TG Love.|29:34:TG Service.|42:46:TG Obedience."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,30,"And behold, thou wilt remember the poor, and consecrate of thy properties for their support that which thou hast to impart unto them, with a covenant and a deed which cannot be broken.","35:39:Prov. 31:20; Mosiah 4:26 (16–26); Alma 1:27; Hel. 4:12. TG Poor.|45:55:Micah 4:13; D&C 72:15; 85:3. TG Consecration.|84:91:TG Welfare."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,31,"And inasmuch as ye impart of your substance unto the poor, ye will do it unto me; and they shall be laid before the bishop of my church and his counselors, two of the elders, or high priests, such as he shall appoint or has appointed and set apart for that purpose.","19:25:Dan. 4:27; Mosiah 2:17.|34:43:Lev. 19:9. TG Generosity.|53:57:Job 29:12. TG Almsgiving; Poor.|100:104:D&C 58:35.|116:122:TG Bishop.|144:154:TG Counselor.|238:247:TG Setting Apart."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,32,"And it shall come to pass, that after they are laid before the bishop of my church, and after that he has received these testimonies concerning the consecration of the properties of my church, that they cannot be taken from the church, agreeable to my commandments, every man shall be made accountable unto me, a steward over his own property, or that which he has received by consecration, as much as is sufficient for himself and family.","148:160:D&C 51:4; 64:15.|290:301:D&C 72:3 (3–11). TG Accountability; Judgment.|313:320:D&C 72:17 (17, 22). TG Stewardship.|432:438:D&C 51:3."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,33,"And again, if there shall be properties in the hands of the church, or any individuals of it, more than is necessary for their support after this first consecration, which is a residue to be consecrated unto the bishop, it shall be kept to administer to those who have not, from time to time, that every man who has need may be amply supplied and receive according to his wants.","177:184:D&C 42:55; 51:13; 82:18 (17–19); 119:1 (1–3)."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,34,"Therefore, the residue shall be kept in my storehouse, to administer to the poor and the needy, as shall be appointed by the high council of the church, and the bishop and his council;","43:53:D&C 42:55; 51:13.|125:137:D&C 102:1 (1–30)."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,35,"And for the purpose of purchasing lands for the public benefit of the church, and building houses of worship, and building up of the New Jerusalem which is hereafter to be revealed—","23:33:D&C 57:5 (5–7); 58:49 (49–51); 101:70 (68–74); 103:23 (22–24).|101:108:TG Worship.|133:146:TG Zion."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,36,That my covenant people may be gathered in one in that day when I shall come to my temple. And this I do for the salvation of my people.,"72:76:D&C 36:8.|83:89:Mal. 3:1."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,37,"And it shall come to pass, that he that sinneth and repenteth not shall be cast out of the church, and shall not receive again that which he has consecrated unto the poor and the needy of my church, or in other words, unto me—","75:83:D&C 41:5; 50:8 (8–9); 64:35. TG Excommunication.|145:156:D&C 51:5."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,38,"For inasmuch as ye do it unto the least of these, ye do it unto me.","19:21:Matt. 25:40 (34–40). TG Love."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,39,"For it shall come to pass, that which I spake by the mouths of my prophets shall be fulfilled; for I will consecrate of the riches of those who embrace my gospel among the Gentiles unto the poor of my people who are of the house of Israel.","124:130:TG Treasure.|190:194:TG Poor."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,40,"And again, thou shalt not be proud in thy heart; let all thy garments be plain, and their beauty the beauty of the work of thine own hands;","29:34:Prov. 16:5. TG Haughtiness; Pride.|42:47:TG Hardheartedness.|61:69:TG Apparel; Clothing; Modesty.|90:96:TG Beauty.|115:119:TG Industry."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,41,And let all things be done in cleanliness before me.,"30:41:TG Cleanliness; Purification."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,42,Thou shalt not be idle; for he that is idle shall not eat the bread nor wear the garments of the laborer.,"18:22:D&C 60:13; 68:30–32; 75:29. TG Idleness; Laziness; Welfare.|62:67:TG Bread.|97:104:TG Labor; Work, Value of."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,43,"And whosoever among you are sick, and have not faith to be healed, but believe, shall be nourished with all tenderness, with herbs and mild food, and that not by the hand of an enemy.","28:32:TG Sickness.|89:98:TG Health.|140:144:TG Food."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,44,"And the elders of the church, two or more, shall be called, and shall pray for and lay their hands upon them in my name; and if they die they shall die unto me, and if they live they shall live unto me.","83:86:TG Hands, Laying on of.|93:98:TG Administrations to the Sick.|133:136:Rom. 14:8 (5–9); D&C 63:49.|148:151:Rev. 14:13."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,45,"Thou shalt live together in love, insomuch that thou shalt weep for the loss of them that die, and more especially for those that have not hope of a glorious resurrection.","11:15:1 Jn. 4:16.|28:32:John 11:36 (35–36). TG Family, Love within; Love.|59:63:Gen. 50:1; Alma 28:11 (11–12); 48:23. TG Mourning.|139:143:1 Cor. 15:19 (19–22). TG Hope."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,46,"And it shall come to pass that those that die in me shall not taste of death, for it shall be sweet unto them;","62:67:John 8:52 (51–52).|71:76:John 11:26; 1 Cor. 15:56. TG Death.|94:99:Job 13:15 (15–16); Rev. 14:13."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,47,"And they that die not in me, wo unto them, for their death is bitter.",""
  doctrineandcovenants,42,48,"And again, it shall come to pass that he that hath faith in me to be healed, and is not appointed unto death, shall be healed.","51:56:D&C 46:19. TG Faith.|69:75:Luke 18:42 (35–43). TG Heal.|88:97:2 Kgs. 20:1 (1–6); Job 7:1; Isa. 38:5; 1 Cor. 4:9; Alma 12:27 (26–28); D&C 121:25.|119:125:TG Death, Power over."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,49,He who hath faith to see shall see.,""
  doctrineandcovenants,42,50,He who hath faith to hear shall hear.,""
  doctrineandcovenants,42,51,The lame who hath faith to leap shall leap.,""
  doctrineandcovenants,42,52,"And they who have not faith to do these things, but believe in me, have power to become my sons; and inasmuch as they break not my laws thou shalt bear their infirmities.","72:77:TG Initiative.|91:95:TG Sons and Daughters of God.|147:151:Rom. 15:1. TG Fellowshipping."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,53,Thou shalt stand in the place of thy stewardship.,"11:16:TG Stewardship; Trustworthiness."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,54,Thou shalt not take thy brother's garment; thou shalt pay for that which thou shalt receive of thy brother.,"34:41:Ex. 22:26.|54:57:D&C 51:11."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,55,"And if thou obtainest more than that which would be for thy support, thou shalt give it into my storehouse, that all things may be done according to that which I have said.","12:21:D&C 82:18 (17–19); 119:1 (1–3).|96:106:D&C 42:34; 51:13."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,56,"Thou shalt ask, and my scriptures shall be given as I have appointed, and they shall be preserved in safety;","23:33:D&C 42:15; 45:60 (60–61).|88:97:TG Scriptures, Preservation of."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,57,"And it is expedient that thou shouldst hold thy peace concerning them, and not teach them until ye have received them in full.","75:78:Moses 1:42; 4:32."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,58,"And I give unto you a commandment that then ye shall teach them unto all men; for they shall be taught unto all nations, kindreds, tongues and people.","96:102:D&C 124:89.|108:111:D&C 1:2, 34 (34–35); 18:28 (26–28); 39:15.|112:119:TG Nations."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,59,"Thou shalt take the things which thou hast received, which have been given unto thee in my scriptures for a law, to be my law to govern my church;","122:125:Josh. 1:8.|139:145:TG God, Law of; Jesus Christ, Head of the Church."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,60,"And he that doeth according to these things shall be saved, and he that doeth them not shall be damned if he so continue.","12:17:D&C 41:5. TG Salvation.|96:102:Moses 5:15. TG Damnation."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,61,"If thou shalt ask, thou shalt receive revelation upon revelation, knowledge upon knowledge, that thou mayest know the mysteries and peaceable things—that which bringeth joy, that which bringeth life eternal.","38:48:D&C 59:4; 76:7; 98:12; 101:32; 121:28 (26–33). TG Revelation.|66:75:Prov. 19:2; Abr. 1:2. TG Knowledge; Learn; Testimony.|118:127:D&C 63:23; 71:1. TG Mysteries of Godliness.|132:141:D&C 36:2; 39:6.|169:172:TG Joy."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,62,"Thou shalt ask, and it shall be revealed unto you in mine own due time where the New Jerusalem shall be built.","81:94:D&C 57:2 (1–5)."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,63,"And behold, it shall come to pass that my servants shall be sent forth to the east and to the west, to the north and to the south.",""
  doctrineandcovenants,42,64,"And even now, let him that goeth to the east teach them that shall be converted to flee to the west, and this in consequence of that which is coming on the earth, and of secret combinations.","95:99:D&C 45:64; 48:2.|128:132:D&C 38:29 (28–30).|170:189:Ether 8:24 (22–25); D&C 5:33 (32–33); 10:6 (6, 25); 38:13, 28."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,65,"Behold, thou shalt observe all these things, and great shall be thy reward; for unto you it is given to know the mysteries of the kingdom, but unto the world it is not given to know them.","68:74:TG Reward.|113:122:Rom. 16:25; Alma 12:9; D&C 6:7 (7–11); 121:27 (25–27)."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,66,Ye shall observe the laws which ye have received and be faithful.,""
  doctrineandcovenants,42,67,"And ye shall hereafter receive church covenants, such as shall be sufficient to establish you, both here and in the New Jerusalem.","38:47:D&C 82:11 (11–15); 84:39; 132:4 (4–7)."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,68,"Therefore, he that lacketh wisdom, let him ask of me, and I will give him liberally and upbraid him not.","27:33:James 1:5; D&C 1:26. TG God, Wisdom of."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,69,"Lift up your hearts and rejoice, for unto you the kingdom, or in other words, the keys of the church have been given. Even so. Amen.","50:57:TG Kingdom of God, on Earth.|82:86:Matt. 16:19; D&C 65:2. TG Priesthood, Keys of."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,70,"The priests and teachers shall have their stewardships, even as the members.","16:24:TG Priest, Aaronic Priesthood; Teacher, Aaronic Priesthood.|42:54:TG Stewardship."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,71,"And the elders or high priests who are appointed to assist the bishop as counselors in all things, are to have their families supported out of the property which is consecrated to the bishop, for the good of the poor, and for other purposes, as before mentioned;","126:135:D&C 41:7.|165:176:TG Consecration."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,72,"Or they are to receive a just remuneration for all their services, either a stewardship or otherwise, as may be thought best or decided by the counselors and bishop.",""
  doctrineandcovenants,42,73,"And the bishop, also, shall receive his support, or a just remuneration for all his services in the church.",""
  doctrineandcovenants,42,74,"Behold, verily I say unto you, that whatever persons among you, having put away their companions for the cause of fornication, or in other words, if they shall testify before you in all lowliness of heart that this is the case, ye shall not cast them out from among you;","86:96:Matt. 5:32.|114:125:TG Fornication; Sexual Immorality."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,75,"But if ye shall find that any persons have left their companions for the sake of adultery, and they themselves are the offenders, and their companions are living, they shall be cast out from among you.","81:89:TG Adulterer.|177:185:TG Excommunication."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,76,"And again, I say unto you, that ye shall be watchful and careful, with all inquiry, that ye receive none such among you if they are married;","44:52:TG Watch."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,77,"And if they are not married, they shall repent of all their sins or ye shall not receive them.",""
  doctrineandcovenants,42,78,"And again, every person who belongeth to this church of Christ, shall observe to keep all the commandments and covenants of the church.",""
  doctrineandcovenants,42,79,"And it shall come to pass, that if any persons among you shall kill they shall be delivered up and dealt with according to the laws of the land; for remember that he hath no forgiveness; and it shall be proved according to the laws of the land.","63:67:Luke 18:20. TG Blood, Shedding of; Murder."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,80,"And if any man or woman shall commit adultery, he or she shall be tried before two elders of the church, or more, and every word shall be established against him or her by two witnesses of the church, and not of the enemy; but if there are more than two witnesses it is better.","37:45:TG Adulterer.|176:185:TG Witness."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,81,"But he or she shall be condemned by the mouth of two witnesses; and the elders shall lay the case before the church, and the church shall lift up their hands against him or her, that they may be dealt with according to the law of God.","109:115:Matt. 18:17 (16–17).|223:226:D&C 64:12."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,82,"And if it can be, it is necessary that the bishop be present also.","43:49:TG Bishop."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,83,And thus ye shall do in all cases which shall come before you.,""
  doctrineandcovenants,42,84,"And if a man or woman shall rob, he or she shall be delivered up unto the law of the land.",""
  doctrineandcovenants,42,85,"And if he or she shall steal, he or she shall be delivered up unto the law of the land.","23:28:TG Stealing."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,86,"And if he or she shall lie, he or she shall be delivered up unto the law of the land.","23:26:TG Honesty; Lying."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,87,"And if he or she do any manner of iniquity, he or she shall be delivered up unto the law, even that of God.","34:42:D&C 43:11."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,88,"And if thy brother or sister offend thee, thou shalt take him or her between him or her and thee alone; and if he or she confess thou shalt be reconciled.","11:18:TG Brotherhood and Sisterhood.|29:35:Matt. 18:15 (15–18). TG Offense.|121:128:TG Confession.|143:153:TG Reconciliation."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,89,"And if he or she confess not thou shalt deliver him or her up unto the church, not to the members, but to the elders. And it shall be done in a meeting, and that not before the world.","144:151:TG Judgment; Justice."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,90,"And if thy brother or sister offend many, he or she shall be chastened before many.","61:70:TG Chastening; Reproof."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,91,"And if any one offend openly, he or she shall be rebuked openly, that he or she may be ashamed. And if he or she confess not, he or she shall be delivered up unto the law of God.","22:28:Ezek. 5:8; 1 Tim. 5:20 (19–21).|87:94:TG Shame."
  doctrineandcovenants,42,92,"If any shall offend in secret, he or she shall be rebuked in secret, that he or she may have opportunity to confess in secret to him or her whom he or she has offended, and to God, that the church may not speak reproachfully of him or her.",""
  doctrineandcovenants,42,93,And thus shall ye conduct in all things.,""
  doctrineandcovenants,43,1,"O hearken, ye elders of my church, and give ear to the words which I shall speak unto you.",""
  doctrineandcovenants,43,2,"For behold, verily, verily, I say unto you, that ye have received a commandment for a law unto my church, through him whom I have appointed unto you to receive commandments and revelations from my hand.","86:89:D&C 42:2 (1–93).|177:188:TG Commandments of God; God, Law of; Revelation."
  doctrineandcovenants,43,3,"And this ye shall know assuredly—that there is none other appointed unto you to receive commandments and revelations until he be taken, if he abide in me.","47:51:TG False Prophets.|88:100:TG Prophets, Mission of.|142:147:John 15:4."
  doctrineandcovenants,43,4,"But verily, verily, I say unto you, that none else shall be appointed unto this gift except it be through him; for if it be taken from him he shall not have power except to appoint another in his stead.","41:45:D&C 28:2 (1–3, 11–13)."
  doctrineandcovenants,43,5,"And this shall be a law unto you, that ye receive not the teachings of any that shall come before you as revelations or commandments;","42:49:D&C 28:5 (3–8).|58:67:TG False Doctrine."
  doctrineandcovenants,43,6,"And this I give unto you that you may not be deceived, that you may know they are not of me.","45:53:D&C 28:11; 46:7. TG Deceit."
  doctrineandcovenants,43,7,"For verily I say unto you, that he that is ordained of me shall come in at the gate and be ordained as I have told you before, to teach those revelations which you have received and shall receive through him whom I have appointed.","43:51:TG Authority; Called of God.|79:83:Matt. 7:13; 2 Ne. 9:41; 31:9 (9, 17–18); 3 Ne. 14:14 (13–14); D&C 22:4.|142:153:TG Scriptures to Come Forth."
  doctrineandcovenants,43,8,"And now, behold, I give unto you a commandment, that when ye are assembled together ye shall instruct and edify each other, that ye may know how to act and direct my church, how to act upon the points of my law and commandments, which I have given.","35:46:TG Commandments of God.|65:74:TG Assembly for Worship; Meetings.|93:101:D&C 88:77 (77–79).|106:111:TG Edification.|141:144:D&C 82:9; JS—H 1:12."
  doctrineandcovenants,43,9,"And thus ye shall become instructed in the law of my church, and be sanctified by that which ye have received, and ye shall bind yourselves to act in all holiness before me—","68:78:TG Sanctification."
  doctrineandcovenants,43,10,"That inasmuch as ye do this, glory shall be added to the kingdom which ye have received. Inasmuch as ye do it not, it shall be taken, even that which ye have received.","44:49:Alma 12:10 (9–11).|127:132:Mark 4:25."
  doctrineandcovenants,43,11,Purge ye out the iniquity which is among you; sanctify yourselves before me;,"0:5:1 Cor. 5:7.|17:25:D&C 42:87. TG Sin."
  doctrineandcovenants,43,12,"And if ye desire the glories of the kingdom, appoint ye my servant Joseph Smith, Jun., and uphold him before me by the prayer of faith.","45:52:TG Sustaining Church Leaders."
  doctrineandcovenants,43,13,"And again, I say unto you, that if ye desire the mysteries of the kingdom, provide for him food and raiment, and whatsoever thing he needeth to accomplish the work wherewith I have commanded him;","49:58:TG Mysteries of Godliness."
  doctrineandcovenants,43,14,"And if ye do it not he shall remain unto them that have received him, that I may reserve unto myself a pure people before me.","103:107:TG Purity.|108:114:TG Millennium, Preparing a People for."
  doctrineandcovenants,43,15,"Again I say, hearken ye elders of my church, whom I have appointed: Ye are not sent forth to be taught, but to teach the children of men the things which I have put into your hands by the power of my Spirit;","37:43:TG Jesus Christ, Head of the Church.|96:102:1 Jn. 2:27. TG Teaching.|111:116:D&C 50:13. TG Missionary Work; Mission of Latter-day Saints; Priesthood, Ordination.|200:206:TG Teaching with the Spirit."
  doctrineandcovenants,43,16,"And ye are to be taught from on high. Sanctify yourselves and ye shall be endowed with power, that ye may give even as I have spoken.","17:23:TG Inspiration; Teachable.|38:46:Josh. 3:5. TG Sanctification.|74:81:Luke 24:49; D&C 38:32; 39:15; 95:8 (8–9); 110:9 (8–10)."
  doctrineandcovenants,43,17,"Hearken ye, for, behold, the great day of the Lord is nigh at hand.","29:34:Mal. 4:5; D&C 2:1; 34:8 (6–9).|35:38:D&C 5:19 (19–20); 29:8; 35:11 (11–16)."
  doctrineandcovenants,43,18,"For the day cometh that the Lord shall utter his voice out of heaven; the heavens shall shake and the earth shall tremble, and the trump of God shall sound both long and loud, and shall say to the sleeping nations: Ye saints arise and live; ye sinners stay and sleep until I shall call again.","49:54:Joel 2:11; D&C 35:21; 88:90; 133:50 (50–52).|88:93:Joel 2:10; 3:16; D&C 45:48. TG Last Days.|114:121:D&C 45:33 (33, 48); 84:118; 88:87 (87, 90).|131:136:D&C 29:13; 45:45.|225:230:TG Resurrection.|252:256:Rev. 20:13 (12–13); Alma 11:41; D&C 76:85; 88:100 (100–101).|261:266:Dan. 12:2; Morm. 9:13 (13–14)."
  doctrineandcovenants,43,19,Wherefore gird up your loins lest ye be found among the wicked.,""
  doctrineandcovenants,43,20,"Lift up your voices and spare not. Call upon the nations to repent, both old and young, both bond and free, saying: Prepare yourselves for the great day of the Lord;","93:97:1 Cor. 12:13."
  doctrineandcovenants,43,21,"For if I, who am a man, do lift up my voice and call upon you to repent, and ye hate me, what will ye say when the day cometh when the thunders shall utter their voices from the ends of the earth, speaking to the ears of all that live, saying—Repent, and prepare for the great day of the Lord?","80:84:TG Hate.|115:118:TG Day of the Lord.|135:143:2 Ne. 27:2; D&C 88:90."
  doctrineandcovenants,43,22,"Yea, and again, when the lightnings shall streak forth from the east unto the west, and shall utter forth their voices unto all that live, and make the ears of all tingle that hear, saying these words—Repent ye, for the great day of the Lord is come?","25:35:Amos 4:6 (6–10)."
  doctrineandcovenants,43,23,"And again, the Lord shall utter his voice out of heaven, saying: Hearken, O ye nations of the earth, and hear the words of that God who made you.","136:140:Deut. 32:6; 1 Ne. 2:12."
  doctrineandcovenants,43,24,"O, ye nations of the earth, how often would I have gathered you together as a hen gathereth her chickens under her wings, but ye would not!","78:81:Matt. 23:37; Luke 13:34; 3 Ne. 10:6 (4–6).|129:138:TG Rebellion."
  doctrineandcovenants,43,25,"How oft have I called upon you by the mouth of my servants, and by the ministering of angels, and by mine own voice, and by the voice of thunderings, and by the voice of lightnings, and by the voice of tempests, and by the voice of earthquakes, and great hailstorms, and by the voice of famines and pestilences of every kind, and by the great sound of a trump, and by the voice of judgment, and by the voice of mercy all the day long, and by the voice of glory and honor and the riches of eternal life, and would have saved you with an everlasting salvation, but ye would not!","15:26:Lev. 26:16; Ezek. 26:6; 1 Ne. 21:26 (25–26); Mosiah 7:29; 11:22 (20–22); Hel. 12:3 (2–4).|50:58:Matt. 23:34. TG Prophets, Mission of.|71:82:D&C 7:6; 130:5.|137:148:Rev. 16:18; 2 Ne. 6:15. TG Nature, Earth.|287:294:Jer. 24:10; Joel 1:10; Amos 4:6; D&C 87:6 (1–8); JS—M 1:29. TG Drought; Famine.|354:359:Ex. 19:19 (13, 16, 19).|411:416:TG Mercy.|479:485:TG Treasure.|536:547:TG Eternal Life; Immortality; Salvation."
  doctrineandcovenants,43,26,"Behold, the day has come, when the cup of the wrath of mine indignation is full.","35:38:Lam. 4:21.|46:51:Ezek. 21:31. TG God, Indignation of."
  doctrineandcovenants,43,27,"Behold, verily I say unto you, that these are the words of the Lord your God.",""
  doctrineandcovenants,43,28,"Wherefore, labor ye, labor ye in my vineyard for the last time—for the last time call upon the inhabitants of the earth.","21:26:Jacob 5:71 (71–75); D&C 27:13; 33:3. TG Vineyard of the Lord."
  doctrineandcovenants,43,29,"For in mine own due time will I come upon the earth in judgment, and my people shall be redeemed and shall reign with me on earth.","32:36:TG Jesus Christ, Second Coming.|55:63:TG Judgment, the Last.|88:96:Rev. 14:4 (2–5).|107:112:TG Jesus Christ, Millennial Reign."
  doctrineandcovenants,43,30,"For the great Millennium, of which I have spoken by the mouth of my servants, shall come.","14:24:TG Millennium."
  doctrineandcovenants,43,31,"For Satan shall be bound, and when he is loosed again he shall only reign for a little season, and then cometh the end of the earth.","4:9:1 Ne. 22:26. TG Devil.|19:24:D&C 45:55; 84:100; 88:110 (110–12); 101:28.|80:93:Rev. 20:3 (3–10); Jacob 5:77 (76–77); D&C 29:22; 88:111 (110–12).|115:118:Matt. 24:14. TG World, End of."
  doctrineandcovenants,43,32,"And he that liveth in righteousness shall be changed in the twinkling of an eye, and the earth shall pass away so as by fire.","22:35:TG Righteousness.|45:52:1 Cor. 15:51 (51–52); D&C 63:51; 88:28 (20, 28); 101:31. TG Resurrection.|120:124:Matt. 3:12."
  doctrineandcovenants,43,33,"And the wicked shall go away into unquenchable fire, and their end no man knoweth on earth, nor ever shall know, until they come before me in judgment.","47:51:Dan. 7:11; D&C 29:28 (21, 26–30). TG Hell.|142:150:TG Jesus Christ, Judge."
  doctrineandcovenants,43,34,"Hearken ye to these words. Behold, I am Jesus Christ, the Savior of the world. Treasure these things up in your hearts, and let the solemnities of eternity rest upon your minds.","58:64:TG Jesus Christ, Savior.|79:87:Isa. 45:22; D&C 6:36; 11:26; JS—M 1:37. TG Treasure.|132:143:D&C 84:61; 88:121; 100:7. TG Levity.|147:155:TG Eternity.|156:160:TG Meditation.|171:176:TG Mind."
  doctrineandcovenants,43,35,Be sober. Keep all my commandments. Even so. Amen.,"3:8:Rom. 12:3; D&C 18:21."
  doctrineandcovenants,44,1,"Behold, thus saith the Lord unto you my servants, it is expedient in me that the elders of my church should be called together, from the east and from the west, and from the north and from the south, by letter or some other way.","111:117:TG Assembly for Worship; Meetings."
  doctrineandcovenants,44,2,"And it shall come to pass, that inasmuch as they are faithful, and exercise faith in me, I will pour out my Spirit upon them in the day that they assemble themselves together.","108:114:Acts 2:17."
  doctrineandcovenants,44,3,"And it shall come to pass that they shall go forth into the regions round about, and preach repentance unto the people.","85:91:TG Preaching."
  doctrineandcovenants,44,4,"And many shall be converted, insomuch that ye shall obtain power to organize yourselves according to the laws of man;","18:27:TG Conversion.|59:64:TG Authority; Church Organization.|88:97:1 Pet. 2:13 (13–14); D&C 51:6; 98:5 (5–7); 109:54."
  doctrineandcovenants,44,5,That your enemies may not have power over you; that you may be preserved in all things; that you may be enabled to keep my laws; that every bond may be broken wherewith the enemy seeketh to destroy my people.,"10:17:Lev. 26:7 (1–13); 2 Ne. 4:33 (16–35)."
  doctrineandcovenants,44,6,"Behold, I say unto you, that ye must visit the poor and the needy and administer to their relief, that they may be kept until all things may be done according to my law which ye have received. Amen.","37:42:James 1:27. TG Compassion; Service; Welfare."
  doctrineandcovenants,45,1,"Hearken, O ye people of my church, to whom the kingdom has been given; hearken ye and give ear to him who laid the foundation of the earth, who made the heavens and all the hosts thereof, and by whom all things were made which live, and move, and have a being.","27:33:TG Jesus Christ, Head of the Church.|47:54:D&C 38:9; 50:35.|144:148:Jer. 14:22; Mosiah 4:2; 3 Ne. 9:15; D&C 14:9. TG Jesus Christ, Creator.|173:178:Gen. 2:1; D&C 38:1; Moses 3:1; Abr. 5:1.|227:231:Acts 17:28."
