  doctrineandcovenants,45,12,"Who were separated from the earth, and were received unto myself—a city reserved until a day of righteousness shall come—a day which was sought for by all holy men, and they found it not because of wickedness and abominations;","9:18:JST Gen. 14:30–34 (Bible Appendix); D&C 38:4; Moses 7:21.|67:71:Heb. 11:16; D&C 84:100; Moses 7:63 (62–64). TG Translated Beings; Zion.|89:92:1 Cor. 5:5."
  doctrineandcovenants,45,13,And confessed they were strangers and pilgrims on the earth;,"24:33:IE sojourners; see Gen. 15:13. 1 Pet. 2:11. TG Stranger."
  doctrineandcovenants,45,14,But obtained a promise that they should find it and see it in their flesh.,"15:22:Heb. 11:13 (8–13); Moses 7:63."
  doctrineandcovenants,45,15,"Wherefore, hearken and I will reason with you, and I will speak unto you and prophesy, as unto men in days of old.","58:63:TG Scriptures to Come Forth."
  doctrineandcovenants,45,16,"And I will show it plainly as I showed it unto my disciples as I stood before them in the flesh, and spake unto them, saying: As ye have asked of me concerning the signs of my coming, in the day when I shall come in my glory in the clouds of heaven, to fulfil the promises that I have made unto your fathers,","50:59:D&C 29:10.|164:169:Matt. 24:3 (3–46); Luke 21:7 (7–36); JS—M 1:4 (4–55). TG Last Days.|219:224:TG Jesus Christ, Glory of; Jesus Christ, Second Coming."
  doctrineandcovenants,45,17,"For as ye have looked upon the long absence of your spirits from your bodies to be a bondage, I will show unto you how the day of redemption shall come, and also the restoration of the scattered Israel.","36:43:Luke 1:79; D&C 138:50.|52:59:TG Spirit Body; Spirits, Disembodied.|166:177:TG Israel, Restoration of.|185:194:Dan. 12:7; 1 Ne. 10:12 (12–14); 22:3 (3–8)."
  doctrineandcovenants,45,18,"And now ye behold this temple which is in Jerusalem, which ye call the house of God, and your enemies say that this house shall never fall.","11:17:Matt. 24:2 (1–2)."
  doctrineandcovenants,45,19,"But, verily I say unto you, that desolation shall come upon this generation as a thief in the night, and this people shall be destroyed and scattered among all nations.","33:43:Ps. 79:3 (1–4); Luke 21:20 (20–24).|140:149:TG Israel, Scattering of."
  doctrineandcovenants,45,20,And this temple which ye now see shall be thrown down that there shall not be left one stone upon another.,"9:15:Matt. 24:1 (1–3); Luke 21:6 (5–6)."
  doctrineandcovenants,45,21,"And it shall come to pass, that this generation of Jews shall not pass away until every desolation which I have told you concerning them shall come to pass.","37:47:Mark 13:30; JS—M 1:34.|148:155:Matt. 24:34."
  doctrineandcovenants,45,22,Ye say that ye know that the end of the world cometh; ye say also that ye know that the heavens and the earth shall pass away;,"29:32:Matt. 24:3. TG World, End of."
  doctrineandcovenants,45,23,"And in this ye say truly, for so it is; but these things which I have told you shall not pass away until all shall be fulfilled.","89:98:Matt. 24:35."
  doctrineandcovenants,45,24,"And this I have told you concerning Jerusalem; and when that day shall come, shall a remnant be scattered among all nations;","96:105:Zech. 2:6; 1 Ne. 10:12 (12–13); 22:4 (3–8); 2 Ne. 25:15 (15–16).|116:123:Gen. 48:19."
